-- India's Kotak Mahindra Bank to buy 15 pct stake in MCX
-- By Nandita Bose
-- Sun Jul 20, 2014 11:52AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 20 (Reuters) - Private sector lender Kotak Mahindra Bank <KTKM.NS> has agreed to buy a 15 percent stake in Multi Commodity Exchange of India (MCX) <MCEI.NS> for 4.59 billion rupees ($76.1 million), the bank said in a statement late on Sunday.

Kotak will purchase the stake from bourse operator Financial Technologies (India) Ltd <FITE.NS> and the deal is subject to regulatory approvals, the statement said. The MCX offers trading in commodity futures including metals, crops and spices.